                                                  INTRODUCTION TO ARRAYS
◻ This will cover:
✅ Introduction
✅ Types 
✅ Declaration 
✅ Traversal
✅ Standard Problems

◻ Introduction :
An array is a collection of items of the same data type stored in contiguous memory locations.

◻ Types:
1) 1D Arrays
    ▫ Stores Elements
    ▫ Accessed using an Index
2) 2D Arrays
3) Multi-Dimensional Array

◻ Declaration
    int arr[5] = { 1,2,4,5,7};
    // Updation of the element at index position 3
    arr[3] = 9;
    
◻ Traversal
    // Function to traverse and print the array
void printArray(int* arr,int n)
{
    int ;
    cout << " Array : " ;
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        cout << arr[i] << "   ";
    }
}


